CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 10, 1953, pg. 5 reads: "Loendi Salute to Eckstine Huge Success at Famous Door - Big Night For Mr. B - When Billy Eckstine came home during Christmas Week for an engagement at the Stanley Theatre, the Loendi Club sponsored a highly successful homecoming week for the famous crooning Pittsburgher. The week of affairs was climaxed by a huge celebration at the Famous Door on Dec. 30.  Man, notables were on hand and Mr. B. received numerous gifts  in token of esteem...William G. Nunn managing editor of the Courier was general chairman of the BIlly Eckstine Homecoming Week..."
TitMainTitle: Billy Eckstine and William G. Nunn standing on stage of Famous Door club, with Billy Eckstine signs in background inscribed "Hear His Latest Hits on M. G. M. Records"
